		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Create a &quot;weaved&quot; spell of the type you want to cast.  Setting it up could be tricky -- need details on how focus effects stack.<br />
<br />
Might just want to split worn and buff focus effects.  Then you could add in &quot;extra buff focus&quot; column...  Would work nicely.<br />
<br />
Then your nuke pattern just takes the chances into account.  If you cast X every weave of power proc, you just add (weave casts)/4 casts of X to your nuke pattern.  The same for the 1/100 negative weaves (you can add in DELAYs if you end up just waiting for it to go away).<br />
<br />
And yes, the &quot;good&quot; nuking patterns will form a convex-up hull.  If one wants a variety of nukes to be used depending on the situation, one needs to place nukes so that nuking patterns using them lie on a convex-up hull.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
