Actually, upon checking, Wildmagic 3 is the first Solteris spell, available for beating the first event - that's the good news. The bad news is that it's priced at 50 phosphenes, and (according to those who beat more than 1 event) each next spell is 25 more expensive than the last. The gear starts from 100 (bracers) and goes up to 200, etc. And the phosphenes drop from raid bosses in clusters of 100, 200, 400 (?), 700(?) - didn't get a confirmation for sure, but it's multiplies of 100. So you can only loot those nice and round amounts of currency. That makes it real inconvenient to buy spells - you get uneven amounts of currency left for the gear, or you have to spend it on stuff like Tendrilmist Rk3 - which is plain stupid.</div>
